race.comment: MORTAL HALO (6) has come back a much stronger colt this prep who can hold a position. Looked to have the race in his keeping inside the 200m when a tenacious winner over 1500m at Rosehill. Has further upside and will handle the rise in weight. TEQUISODA (13) talented colt who comes to town third-up. Relished the extra trip when he attacked the line for a narrow second over 1500m at Newcastle. Blinkers go on and will take holding out on the limit. Solid top-three player. WILLIE OPPA (10) third-up now and a win looks imminent. Raced without luck from the low draw when fourth to MORTAL HALO over 1500m at Rosehill. No shock to see him turn the tables today. COVERT THINKING (2) gritty effort first-up and comes out of a solid rating contest when third to Hyperbolic over 1400m at Rosehill. Undefeated over the mile and stays in the mix with Stanley's claim. FULL HAO (1) good mare back in trip for this after winning over 1800m at Rosehill last start. Grima stays aboard and must respect.
